snippet.textDisplay:
Not so much a fan of "windy" top managers like Ghosn, but to be fair the Japanese justice system is not the best in the world. Yes, 99,9% of all accused persons get sentenced. But not because the police only brings up cases where they are "confindent". That is propaganda. It is a system based on shame. If you are accusing someone and in the course of the investigation it happens that you find out that he is not guilty, you certainly would accuse him anyway, because otherwise the police, the prosecutors, the judges and the state itself would be ashamed. That is why innocent people cant get out of prison in Japan. Also Japan has the highest suicidal quote in prisons. Japanese authorities are notorious for using torture. Even later in the prisons. There are no fair processes in Japanese courts. And it saddens me quite a bit that the propaganda is spreading around the world and serves even as a "good" example. I wish people would think what a rate of over 90% means. And I wish people would educate on topics they are talking about.
I like Japanese culture and Japan itself. But the legal system is utter shit.

snippet.textDisplay:
I hate my 280zxt :-/ All those wizbang robot features to sell it off the lot died on it, just becoming dead weight on a sportscar. The real nail in the coffin was when the gas unit sender failed and nothing I did fixed it, and the head light switch, and the digital dash (ditto and ditto).

I switched to driving 40 year old Honda motor cycles and never went back. The Honda motorcycles are everything I wanted my zcars to be but weren't... fun, thrifty on gas, turn heads, fast acceleration, easy to work on, cheap to maintain.

So what to do with my 40 year old 280zxt and 300z and B210? :-/ The B210 was an awesome drift car, but as light as it was it still only got 25mpg. My motorcycles get 50-60mpg.
snippet.textOriginal:
I hate my 280zxt :-/   All those wizbang robot features to sell it off the lot died on it, just becoming dead weight on a sportscar.   The real nail in the coffin was when the gas unit sender failed and nothing I did fixed it, and the head light switch, and the digital dash (ditto and ditto).    

I switched to driving 40 year old Honda motor cycles and never went back.    The Honda motorcycles are everything I wanted my zcars to be but weren't... fun, thrifty on gas, turn heads, fast acceleration, easy to work on, cheap to maintain.

So what to do with my 40 year old 280zxt and 300z and B210?  :-/  The B210 was an awesome drift car, but as light as it was it still only got 25mpg.    My motorcycles get 50-60mpg.

snippet.textDisplay: As you pointed out, Nissan was losing money even when they were still making decent cars. SO it's not simply making something reliable and fun to drive that matters. You have to make something that's exciting to people as well. And as much as I like performance cars and trucks, no mass market automaker is going to sell enough Z-car or Raptor type vehicles to survive. Make a better Camry or Accord. Build a better CR-V or Highlander. We know what sells so do it better. Be the automaker that forces your competitors to step up their game and not the one that always needs to play catch up. Stop with the good enough game and the profit through cost cutting alone game. Short term that get's you back on track but long term it's recipe for disaster. The methods Goshen had in place were still more or less there for the beginning of Nissan's recent decline meaning that the cycle of his company saving measures were coming to an end with no vision for growth and continued success on the horizon. The new Titan is never going to rule the truck market of the big 3 but that doesn't mean it shouldn't have taken a bite out of it. But they didn't really even try. It was another moment of, well, it's pretty good (and it is) so that's good enough for us. The XD should have been a true 250/2500 series level pickup or just scrapped altogether. There was never a market for an in-between truck. If they want to experiment with trucks how about an actual compact truck aimed at the needs of small business and the guys who just want a hardworking and affordable truck. Heck, put a 49 inch wide bed on the Frontier so you can lay four foot wide sheet goods flat in the bed. The space between the wheels is already there with room to spare for articulation. Any line about why not is a lie. Bring back the Datsun name for a performance division and offer the Z's , GTR's and perhaps a few other models as Datsuns. SO much that could be done but I don't have any real hope that it will be. Yeah, a hot new Z-car would be awesome but it won't save the company. And if it costs 50k plus just to get the base model it won't support itself.

snippet.textDisplay:
Get out from under Renault, stop putting JATCO CVT transmissions in everything they make, and go back to quality first mentality like Toyota. Sports cars are only a small percentage of total sales Nissan makes, so it makes sense to focus on cars people can afford that are on par with the quality that Toyota and Honda produce. For God's sake, stop making cars in Mexico where every car manufacturer has suffered from poor quality issues once they started production there. It may look good on paper now, but it'll bite them in the ass later and further degrade their image as a company. Quality, quality, quality even if it means they have to raise the price of their vehicles overall to stay in business. Lastly, do marketing campaigns around quality and innovation which they can demonstrate with short infomercials about how they're improving quality and getting back to the roots they once had as a company.

All of this can only happen by separating themselves Renault which is a piss poor company with shoddy quality control who's losing money by the buttloads.
